					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">crudelios wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Also, when you start a sample using STA $4015, if the output buffer is empty so the APU will have to load a new sample from memory, you should immediately delay CPU execution by 3 cycles, not 4.</div>
<br />
<br />My notes: <div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;/* 3 if it lands on a CPU write, <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2 if it lands on the $4014 write or during OAM DMA, <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1 if on the next-to-next-to-last DMA cycle, <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 3 if on the last DMA cycle.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;DMA transfer takes 513 cycles on even cycles<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;and 514 on odd cycles. */<br /><br />&nbsp;/* You can see this in the STA $100 after OAM DMA,<br />&nbsp; where DMC DMA takes three cycles for two different times.<br />&nbsp; This is because both times it's landing on the fourth cycle of STA $100.<br />&nbsp; */</div></div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><strong>Zepper</strong><br /><a href="http://rocknes.web.fc2.com/" class="postlink"><em>RockNES developer</em></a></div>
